<Layout title="ROSIX Whitepaper - UOS Technical Specification Draft" description="ROSIX (Resource Operating System Interface) Whitepaper v1.2, Technical specification draft for Human-Cyber-Physical Convergence Operating System for Power Information Scenarios">
  <main class="container">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>ROSIX Whitepaper v1.2 (Draft Standard)</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Resource Operating System Interface - UOS Technical Specification Draft</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <section class="version-history">
        <h2>Version History</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>v1.0</strong>：Initial draft, released in January 2025, defining ROSIX core interfaces and concepts.</li>
          <li><strong>v1.1</strong>：Revised version, August 21, 2025, expanded details, added examples, enhanced professionalism.</li>
          <li><strong>v1.2</strong>：Current version, December 2025, refined technical details, added industry use cases and ecosystem guidelines.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="overview">
        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>ROSIX (Resource Operating System Interface) is the core technical specification for the Human-Cyber-Physical Convergence Operating System (UOS) targeting power information scenarios. It provides unified resource abstraction, spatiotemporal management, real-time stream processing, rule engine, workflow orchestration, and AI integration capabilities, supporting complex system construction in industrial internet scenarios.</p>
        
        <h3>1.1 Design Philosophy</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Scenario as Computer</strong>：Abstract physical world scenarios as programmable computing environments</li>
          <li><strong>Software-Defined Systems</strong>：Achieve flexible system behavior adjustment through software configuration</li>
          <li><strong>Human-Machine-Physical Collaboration</strong>：Support seamless collaboration between humans, machines, and physical entities</li>
          <li><strong>Ubiquitous Connectivity</strong>：Provide unified resource access and communication interfaces</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Technical Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Resource Abstraction</strong>：Unified resource model supporting devices, data, services, and other resource types</li>
          <li><strong>Spatiotemporal Management</strong>：Resource organization and querying based on spatiotemporal coordinates</li>
          <li><strong>Real-time Stream Processing</strong>：Support for high-concurrency, low-latency data stream processing</li>
          <li><strong>Rule Engine</strong>：Declarative rule definition and automatic execution</li>
          <li><strong>Workflow Orchestration</strong>：Automated orchestration and execution of complex tasks</li>
          <li><strong>AI Integration</strong>：Built-in AI capabilities supporting intelligent decision-making and optimization</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="architecture">
        <h2>2. System Architecture</h2>
        <p>ROSIX adopts a layered architecture design, from bottom to top including:</p>
        
        <h3>2.1 Core Layer (ROSIX.Core)</h3>
        <p>Provides basic resource operation interfaces, including resource opening, reading, writing, invocation, and subscription.</p>
        
        <h3>2.2 Resource Space Layer (ResourceSpace)</h3>
        <p>Provides resource management and querying capabilities based on spatiotemporal coordinates.</p>
        
        <h3>2.3 Stream Processing Layer (Stream)</h3>
        <p>Supports real-time data stream processing and analysis.</p>
        
        <h3>2.4 Rule Engine Layer (Rule)</h3>
        <p>Provides declarative rule definition and automatic execution capabilities.</p>
        
        <h3>2.5 Workflow Layer (Workflow)</h3>
        <p>Supports orchestration and automated execution of complex tasks.</p>
        
        <h3>2.6 AI Integration Layer (AI)</h3>
        <p>Provides AI agent and intelligent decision-making capabilities.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="examples">
        <h2>3. Application Examples</h2>
        
        <h3>3.1 Power Inspection Scenario</h3>
        <p>Using drone inspection of substations as an example, demonstrating the complete application process of ROSIX:</p>
        
        <h4>3.1.1 Resource Management</h4>
        <p>Open and manage resources such as drones and sensors through ROSIX.Core interfaces.</p>
        
        <h4>3.1.2 Real-time Stream Processing</h4>
        <p>Use Stream module to process real-time data streams such as temperature and video.</p>
        
        <h4>3.1.3 Rule Definition</h4>
        <p>Define business rules such as overheating alerts through the Rule engine.</p>
        
        <h4>3.1.4 Workflow Orchestration</h4>
        <p>Use Workflow module to orchestrate complete inspection processes.</p>
        
        <h4>3.1.5 AI Integration</h4>
        <p>Implement intelligent analysis such as defect detection through the AI module.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="security">
        <h2>4. Security and Consistency</h2>
        
        <h3>4.1 Permission Model</h3>
        <p>Based on JWT AccessToken, supporting Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).</p>

        <h3>4.2 Isolation Mechanisms</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Domain</strong>：Resource domain isolation, ensuring resources from different business domains do not interfere</li>
          <li><strong>Namespace</strong>：Namespace isolation, supporting multi-tenant environments</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Consistency Guarantees</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Strong Consistency</strong>：Based on Raft algorithm, used for critical control operations</li>
          <li><strong>Eventual Consistency</strong>：Based on Gossip protocol, used for data stream processing</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Audit and Compliance</h3>
        <p>Operation logs are recorded, complying with the following standards:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)</li>
          <li>ISO 27001 (Information Security Management System)</li>
          <li>GB/T 2887-2011 (Power Equipment Inspection Specification)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="implementation">
        <h2>5. Implementation and Ecosystem</h2>
        
        <h3>5.1 Development Environment</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>ROSIX SDK</strong>：Core development toolkit</li>
          <li><strong>Multi-language Bindings</strong>：Support for C++, Rust, Java, Python</li>
          <li><strong>Testing Framework</strong>：Unit testing (JUnit), Mock testing (Mockito)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.2 Deployment Solutions</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Containerization</strong>：Support for Docker containerized deployment</li>
          <li><strong>Cluster Management</strong>：Support for Kubernetes cluster orchestration</li>
          <li><strong>Performance Metrics</strong>：Response time < 100ms, throughput > 1000 events/s</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.3 Open Source Ecosystem</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Core Repository</strong>：<a href="https://github.com/uos-projects/uos-rosix" target="_blank">https://github.com/uos-projects/uos-rosix</a></li>
          <li><strong>Java Binding</strong>：<a href="https://github.com/uos-projects/rosix-java-binding" target="_blank">https://github.com/uos-projects/rosix-java-binding</a></li>
          <li><strong>Contribution Methods</strong>：Submit Issues or Pull Requests</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="api-reference">
        <h2>6. API Reference</h2>
        
        <table class="api-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Module</th>
              <th>Representative Interfaces</th>
              <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>ROSIX.Core</td>
              <td>rosix_open / rosix_read / rosix_invoke / rosix_subscribe</td>
              <td>Basic resource operations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>ResourceSpace</td>
              <td>rosix_resolve / rosix_update_spatial / rosix_update_temporal</td>
              <td>Spatiotemporal management</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Stream</td>
              <td>rosix_stream_open / rosix_stream_subscribe</td>
              <td>Real-time stream processing</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Rule</td>
              <td>rosix_rule_define / rosix_rule_enable</td>
              <td>Rule definition and enabling</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Workflow</td>
              <td>rosix_workflow_create / rosix_workflow_add_task</td>
              <td>Workflow orchestration</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>AI</td>
              <td>rosix_agent_invoke / rosix_agent_bind</td>
              <td>AI agent invocation and binding</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="glossary">
        <h2>7. Glossary</h2>
        <dl>
          <dt><strong>Resource</strong></dt>
          <dd>Abstract entity containing URI, attributes, and behavior, the basic operation unit of the ROSIX system</dd>
          
          <dt><strong>Actor Model</strong></dt>
          <dd>Concurrent computing model based on message passing, supporting high concurrency and distributed computing</dd>
          
          <dt><strong>Digital Twin</strong></dt>
          <dd>Digital mapping of physical entities, enabling virtual-physical fusion collaborative computing</dd>
          
          <dt><strong>AccessToken</strong></dt>
          <dd>JWT format permission token used for identity authentication and authorization</dd>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="future">
        <h2>8. Future Outlook</h2>
        <p>UOS and ROSIX will continue to evolve, with planned expansions in the following areas:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Enhanced AI Capabilities</strong>：Integration of advanced AI technologies such as reinforcement learning and federated learning</li>
          <li><strong>Hardware Support</strong>：Support for 5G/6G networks and edge computing devices</li>
          <li><strong>Ecosystem Integration</strong>：Integration with mainstream platforms such as AWS and EdgeX Foundry</li>
          <li><strong>Standard Development</strong>：Promotion as an international standard (such as IEEE P2413)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="references">
        <h2>9. References</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>POSIX Standard (IEEE 1003.1)</li>
          <li>GB/T 2887-2011 (Power Equipment Inspection Specification)</li>
